The global endocarditis drug market is segmented based on several key factors that influence the market dynamics. The segmentation by drug type includes antibiotics, antifungals, and others. Antibiotics are the most commonly used drugs for treating endocarditis, while antifungals are crucial for fungal endocarditis cases. The market is also segmented by the route of administration, with options such as oral and injectable medications. The distribution channel segment comprises hospital pharmacies, retail pharmacies, and online pharmacies, highlighting the diverse purchasing options available to consumers. Lastly, the end-user segment categorizes the market into hospitals, specialty clinics, and others, reflecting the varied healthcare settings where endocarditis treatment is provided.

